column15: There appears to be some limitations with representing these thiophene annulenes with smiles as originally drawn, which then affects the InChI double bond configuration layer between toolkits. Molfile maintains the configuration, however, based on other PubChem submitted substances, the standardization process changes the configuration again (* examples already in PubChem). So I donâ€™t see a need to submit the molfiles directly from ChemAxon. I think this is just a cheminformatics drawing layout preference issue with these highly symmetric/conjugated molecules and it is safe to proceed with current workflow.
